Priority: optional
Maintainer: Dakota Smith <smith.dakota52@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/jedijamez/copilot-key-handler

Package: copilot-key-handler
Architecture: all
Depends: python3, python3-evdev, python3-yaml, xdotool, x11-utils, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Maps the Windows Copilot key to launch Claude Code on Linux
 Listens for the KEY_F23 event generated by the Windows Copilot key
 (found on ASUS ROG and other modern laptops) and opens a terminal
 running Claude Code. Supports auto-detection of the keyboard device,
 user, and Claude Code path. Configurable via /etc/copilot-key-handler/config.yaml.
